### Instructions:
You are provided with the list of intents. Your task will be to classify the user input below. I also want you to extract all relevant entities for the chosen category.
	• Each intent has a unique ID associated with it in alphanumeric format. Each category has its name and description.
If no category can be identified, please return: {“prediction_category”: “none _of_the_above”}.
	• For each intent there are also attributes associated with them. Those are unique values that need to be retrieved for a particular category. Each Attribute has a unique  Attribute-Id, attribute description and may also include "attribute_possible_values", which means the attribute must match one of the provided values.  It may also include 'attribute-similar-values', which mean the examples are given but the extracted attributes do not need to exactly match those given values. If multiple attributes are provided, fill all the attributes. If an attribute value is not provided, set the value of the slot to "none".
Use the following format for your response:


{
"output": [
    {
        "category": "category_id",
        "attributes": [
            {
                "attribute id 1": "value 1",
                "attribute id 2": "value 2"...
            }
        ]
    }
]
}
### input
Unresponsive areas on my Samsung screen. Any quick fixes?
